The Office of
the National Coordinator for HIT,

2
00:00:03,270 --> 00:00:09,030
ONC, defines a fourth way of
classifying HIEs, by function.

3
00:00:09,030 --> 00:00:12,790
The first category is Directed Exchange,
used to send and

4
00:00:12,790 --> 00:00:16,650
receive information between
providers for care coordination.

5
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:20,240
Later, Marla will return to
help us see how that works.

6
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,340
The second is Query-based HIE.

7
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:26,620
This is data aggregation
among providers.

8
00:00:26,620 --> 00:00:30,180
The third is Consumer Mediated
Health Information Exchange,

9
00:00:30,180 --> 00:00:33,430
which refers to data
aggregation by patients.

10
